tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  78,32,"It is full of gardens and grapevines."
  78,33,"And women of similar ages."
  78,34,"And full glasses of wine."
  79,1,"Allah takes an oath on the angels who pull out the souls of the disbelievers with severity and harshness."
  79,2,"And He also takes an oath on the angels who gently remove the souls of the believers with ease and smoothness."
  79,4,"And He also takes an oath on the angels who compete with one another to carry out the command of Allah."
  79,6,"On the day when the earth will tremble upon the first blowing of the horn."
  79,7,"The second blow will follow it."
  79,8,"The hearts of some people will be fearful on that day."
  79,9,"The effects of humiliation will be apparent on their faces."
  79,10,"They would say: “Will we be returned to life after we have died?”"
  79,13,"The matter of the resurrection is easy. It will only be a single scream from the angel appointed to blow."